 William \u2013 Mi Gente (Steve Aoki Remix)\"] elportaldemusica.es. Retrieved January 4, 2018.</ref>}}\n{{Certification Table Bottom|streaming=true}}\n\n==Release history==\n{|class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\"\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Region\n! scope=\"row\"| Date\n! scope=\"row\"| Format\n! scope=\"row\"| Version\n! scope=\"row\"| Label\n! scope=\"row\"| {{abbr|Ref.|Reference(s)}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Various\n| June 30, 2017\n| [[Music download|Digital download]]\n| rowspan=\"3\"| Original\n| {{hlist|Scorpio|Universal Latin}}\n| <ref name=\"original\"/>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Italy\n| July 14, 2017\n| rowspan=\"2\"| [[Contemporary hit radio]]\n| [[Universal Music Group|Universal]]\n| <ref>http://radiodate.it/radio-date/j-balvin-willy-william-mi-gente-176571-14-07-2017-radiodate/</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| United States\n| July 18, 2017\n| [[Republic Records|Republic]]\n| <ref name=\"us radio\"/>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=\"7\"| Various\n| rowspan=\"6\"| October 20, 2017\n| rowspan=\"7\"| Digital download\n| [[Alesso]] Remix\n| rowspan=\"7\"| {{hlist|Scorpio|Universal}}\n| <ref name=\"Alesso\"/>\n|-\n| [[Cedric Gervais]] Remix\n| <ref name=\"Cedric Gervais\"/>\n|-\n| [[Dillon Francis]] Remix\n| <ref name=\"Dillon Francis\"/>\n|-\n| Henry Fong Remix\n| <ref name=\"Henry Fong\"/>\n|-\n| [[Steve Aoki]] Remix\n| <ref name=\"Steve Aoki\"/>\n|-\n| [[Sunnery James & Ryan Marciano]] Remix\n| <ref name=\"SJ&RM\"/>\n|-\n| November 3, 2017\n| [[Hardwell]] & [[Quintino (DJ)|Quintino]] Remix\n| <ref name=\"H&Q\"/>\n|}\n\n==Beyonc\u00e9 remix==\n{{Infobox song\n| name          = Mi Gente (Remix)\n| cover         = Mi-gente-beyonce.jpg\n| alt           =\n| border        = yes\n| type          = single\n| artist        = [[J Balvin]] and [[Willy William]] featuring [[Beyonc\u00e9]]\n| album         =\n| language      = {{hlist|Spanish|English}}\n| English_title = \"My People\"\n| released      = {{Start date|2017|09|28}}\n| format        = [[Music download|Digital download]]\n| recorded      =\n| studio        =\n| venue         =\n| genre         = {{hlist|[[Reggaeton]]|[[moombahton]]|[[Contemporary R&B|R&B]]}}\n| length        = {{Duration|m=3|s=30}}<ref name=\"Beyonc\u00e9\"/>\n| label         = {{hlist|[[Universal Music Latin Entertainment|Universal Latin]]|[[Scorpio Music|Scorpio]]|[[Columbia Records|Columbia]]|[[Parkwood Entertainment|Parkwood]]}}\n| writer        = {{hlist|J Balvin|Willy William|[[Mohombi]] [[DJ Assad]]|Andr\u00e9s David Restrepo|[[Terius Nash]]|Beyonc\u00e9 {{small|({{abbr|add.|additional}})}}}}\n| producer      = {{hlist|Willy William|Beyonc\u00e9 {{small|({{abbr|add.|additional}})}}}}\n| prev_title    =\n| prev_year     =\n| next_title    =\n| next_year     =\n| misc          = {{Extra chronology\n | artist     = [[Beyonc\u00e9]]\n | type       = single\n | prev_title = [[Shining (song)|Shining]]\n | prev_year  = 2017\n | title      = Mi Gente (Remix)\n | year       = 2017\n | next_title = [[Walk on Water (Eminem song)|Walk on Water]]\n | next_year  = 2017\n}}\n{{External music video|{{YouTube|APHgDFRpCi0|\"Mi Gente (Remix)\"}}\n}}\n}}\n\nOn September 28, 2017, a remix version featuring vocals by American singer [[Beyonc\u00e9]] was released on digital stores and streaming services. The remix was released as a single by Universal Music Latin, [[Republic Records]], [[Columbia Records]], and [[Parkwood Entertainment]]. Beyonc\u00e9 donated all proceeds from the song to hurricane relief charities in Mexico, Puerto Rico, and other Caribbean islands. Balvin and William stated Beyonc\u00e9 was the \"top choice\" for the remix, and had no expectation of her agreeing to the song when they reached out to her.\n\nBeyonc\u00e9 would later perform the song in her [[Beyonc\u00e9 2018 Coachella performance|set]] in [[Coachella Valley Music and Arts Festival|Coachella]] in 2018. For the second weekend, Balvin joined her on stage.\n\nThis song is also part of the set list for the [[OTR II]] tour. The song was added to the set list at the show in [[Manchester]] on June 13, 2018 at [[City of Manchester Stadium|Etihad Stadium]].\n\n===Commercial performance===\nUpon the release of the remixed version of the song featuring [[Beyonc\u00e9]], the song reached number one on the Hot Latin Songs chart, ending the 35-week reign led by \"[[Despacito]]\", becoming Balvin's fourth number one on the Hot Latin Songs chart, as well as Beyonc\u00e9's highest-charting song on the chart after \"[[Irreplaceable]]\" peaked at number four and \"[[Beautiful Liar]]\" peaked at number 10 in 2007. On the Hot 100, the remix moved from number 21 to number three after a full tracking week, giving both Balvin and William their first top 10 single and Beyonc\u00e9 her 17th top 10 single (27th with Destiny's Child) on the chart. The remix also reached number one the US [[Digital Songs]] chart with 79,000 copies sold during that week (combined sales with the original version), becoming both Balvin and William's first number one song on that respective chart, and Beyonc\u00e9's sixth, as well as just the second mostly-Spanish sung song to top the chart after \"Despacito\".<ref name=\"Hot 100 peak\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/7990506/j-balvin-willy-william-beyonce-cardi-b-hot-100|title=J Balvin, Willy William & Beyonce Blast to No. 3 on Hot 100 With 'Mi Gente,' Cardi B No. 1 for Third Week|work=Billboard|last=Trust|first=Gary|date=October 9, 2017|accessdate=October 10, 2017}}</ref> This made \"Mi Gente\", alongside \"Despacito\", as the first time in the Hot 100 chart history for two non-English singles to appear in the top 10 simultaneously.\n\nIn Canada, the remix reached a new peak of number two on the Canadian Hot 100, behind [[Post Malone]] and [[21 Savage]]'s \"[[Rockstar (Post Malone song)|Rockstar]]\", becoming both Balvin and William's highest charting single at the time, and Beyonc\u00e9's 13th top 10 single. It also moved from number 17 to number one on the Hot Digital Songs chart.<ref>http://www.fyimusicnews.ca/articles/2017/10/10/shania-hedley-and-tom-petty-loom-large-weeks-chart</ref>\n\nThe remix also peaked at number one in many European and Latin American countries, including Argentina, Hungary, Mexico, the Netherlands, Bolivia, Panama, Paraguay, Costa Rica, and Australia.\n\n===Music video===\nA music video was also released on YouTube featuring American producer [[Diplo]], French DJ [[David Guetta]], Dutch DJ [[Martin Garrix]], Dutch DJ [[Ti\u00ebsto]], Venezuelan YouTuber [[Lele Pons]], Brazilian soccer player [[Neymar]], Brazilian singer [[Anitta (singer)|Anitta]], Colombian singer [[Piso 21|El Llane]],  [[Portuguese people|Portuguese]] footballer [[Cristiano Ronaldo]] and several fan made videos.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/latin/7981833/the-video-for-the-beyonce-remix-of-mi-gente-is-jam-packed-with|title=The Video for the Beyonc\u00e9 Remix of 'Mi Gente' Is Jam-Packed With Recognizable Faces|publisher=|via=Billboard}}</ref>\n\n===Critical reception===\nThe version featuring Beyonc\u00e9 was named \"Best New Track\" by ''[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]'' with Matthew Ismael Ruiz stating that the song \"is about a shared cultural pride, one that transcends borders and race, from J Balvin's native Colombia to Puerto Rico and across all of Latinidad. It's a declaration that \"El mundo nos quiere\" (The world wants us) set to a head-nod bop. Beyonc\u00e9 gets this, and with this remix, she backs up her words with action. This is what solidarity sounds like.\"<ref>https://pitchfork.com/reviews/tracks/j-balvin-and-willy-williams-mi-gente-ft-beyonce-remix/</ref> Randall Roberts from ''[[Los Angeles Times]]'' wrote that: \"To say Beyonc\u00e9 lends a hand in the remix is an understatement. Unlike guests who limit their contributions to a single late-track verse or hook, Beyonc\u00e9 upends \"Mi Gente\" from the first verse and proceeds to bilingually maneuver through the rhythmic, up-tempo jam like the queen she is.\"<ref>https://www.latimes.com/entertainment/la-et-entertainment-news-updates-listen-beyonce-remix-j-balvin-1506699503-htmlstory.html</ref>\n\nIn 2019, ''[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]'' listed ''Mi Gente (Remix)'' at number 189 on their greatest songs of the decade (2010s) list.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://pitchfork.com/features/lists-and-guides/the-200-best-songs-of-the-2010s/|title=The 200 Best Songs of the 2010s|website=Pitchfork|date=October 7, 2019|accessdate=October 8, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Awards and nominations===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Ceremony\n! Award\n! Result\n! Ref\n|-\n| rowspan=\"13\"| 2018\n| [[American Society of Composers, Authors and Publishers|ASCAP Latin Awards]]\n| Most Performed Songs\n| {{won}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| <ref>http://ascap.com/latinawards18</ref>\n|-\n| [[Billboard Music Awards]]\n| Top Latin Song\n| {{nom}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/bbma/8343598/billboard-music-awards-2018-nominations-list</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"6\"| [[Billboard Latin Music Awards]]\n| Hot Latin Song of the Year\n| {{nom}}\n| rowspan=\"6\" style=\"text-align:center;\"| <ref>https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/latin/8098517/2018-billboard-latin-music-awards-nominations</ref>\n|-\n| Hot Latin Song of the Year, Vocal Event\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Airplay Song of the Year\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Digital Song of the Year\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Streaming Song of the Year\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Latin Rhythm Song of the Year\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[iHeartRadio Music Awards]]\n| Best Remix\n| {{nom}}\n| <ref>https://www.iheart.com/content/2018-03-10-2018-iheartradio-music-awards-see-the-full-list-of-nominees-winners/</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| [[Latin American Music Award]]s\n| Song of the Year\n| {{nom}}\n| rowspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>https://www.telemundo.com/shows/latin-american-music-awards/vota-en-todas-las-categorias</ref>\n|-\n| Favorite Urban Song\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Latin Grammy Award]]s\n| Best Urban Fusion/Performance\n| {{nom}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>https://www.latingrammy.com/en/news/j-balvin-leads-latin-grammy-nominations-with-eight-followed-by-rosal-a-with-five-el-david</ref>\n|-\n| [[MTV Millennial Awards]]\n| Hit of the Year\n| {{nom}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>http://miaw.mtvla.com/noticias/estos0son-los-nominados-a-los-premios-mtv-miaw-2018</ref>\n|}\n\n===Track listing===\n{{Track listing\n| headline        = Digital download<ref name=\"Beyonc\u00e9\">{{Cite news |url= https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/mi-gente-feat-beyonc%C3%A9/id1291110776?i=1291110777 |title= Mi Gente (feat. Beyonc\u00e9) \u2013 Single|website=iTunes (US)}}</ref>\n| title1          = Mi Gente\n| note1           = featuring [[Beyonc\u00e9]]\n| length1         = 3:29\n}}\n\n===Charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2017\u201318)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Argentina ([[Monitor Latino]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://charts.monitorlatino.com/top20/Argentina/General/20171009|publisher=[[Monitor Latino]]|accessdate=16 October 2017|title=Top 20 Argentina \u2013 Del 9 al 15 de Octubre, 2017|language=Spanish|date=9 October 2017}}</ref>\n| 1\n|-\n{{single chart|Australia|11|artist=J Balvin & Willy William feat. Beyonc\u00e9|song=Mi gente|rowheader=true|accessdate=12 October 2017|refname=AustraliaRemix|note=<!-- Original peak before ARIA began crediting Beyonce -->}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Austria|4|artist=J Balvin & Willy William feat. Beyonc\u00e9|song=Mi gente|rowheader=true|accessdate=12 October 2017|refname=AustriaRemix}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Flanders|8|artist=J Balvin & Willy William feat. Beyonc\u00e9|song=Mi gente|rowheader=true|accessdate=1 September 2017|refname=FlandersJBWWB}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Wallonia|7|artist=J Balvin & Willy William feat. Beyonc\u00e9|song=Mi gente|rowheader=true|accessdate=1 September 2017|refname